description: Test the light sensor inside the ambient sensor module by varying ambient light and observing if the relay or indicator LED responds accordingly., outcome='The control relay was visually inspected and is currently in a closed state with no observable internal fault. The ambient light sensor was also inspected and shows no internal fault. No polarity inversion detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Ambient Sensor Module Power Supply/Switching Circuit,
description: Test the internal power supply and control/switching circuit (other than relay and sensor) in the ambient sensor module for stability or intermittent issues, focusing especially on power delivery and controller stability., outcome='All control input and output cables show nominal continuity. No polarity inversion detected for any cable connections. Voltage measurements confirm expected supply and ground levels at control input cables, and low voltages at control output cables; all resistances and voltages are within expected parameters for the tested components.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=320.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Switched Cables Indicator LED (Ambient Sensor Module),
description: Test the switched cables indicator LED inside the ambient sensor module for intermittent operation corresponding to the lamp cycling. Observe if the indicator LED flashes or changes state in sync with the main lamp's periodic switching off and on., outcome='The Ambient Light Sensor and Main Load (lamp) were visually inspected with no observable internal faults. The main lamp is currently not lit. There is no mention of any polarity inversion in the described connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> Load Module Lamp Indicator,
description: Visually inspect the lamp indicator inside the load module via the peephole or access panel to determine if the indicator bulb exhibits the same intermittent behavior as the main lamp., outcome='Both the Internal Indicator Lamp and the Main Load (lamp) were successfully observed and are not lit, with no observable internal faults detected. The Load Cube does not have a peephole that can be opened, but access was gained via the inspection panel. The Internal Indicator Lamp is connected in parallel with the main load and reflects voltage conditions across that branch.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_peephole', 5.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load Module Input Diode,
description: Test the diode at the input of the load module to check for intermittent operation or high forward resistance, which could cause both the lamp and the indicator to periodically turn off., outcome='The diode at the input of the load module tested nominal in forward direction, with a measured forward voltage of 0.7 V matching the nominal value. No issues detected with diode forward resistance or operation.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_diode', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Load Module Main Lamp,
description: Test the main lamp in the load module for intermittent contact or internal faults, such as loose filament or thermal cycling effects., outcome='The main load lamp shows no observable internal faults on visual inspection. Continuity testing indicates nominal resistance (120 Ω), matching the expected value. No intermittent contact or loose filament was detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Ambient Sensor Module Relay,
description: Test the relay for potential intermittent operation or unstable switching, by monitoring its contact voltage and continuity during the lamp's cycling period., outcome='The voltage measurements at the control relay are 11.9873 V at the positive terminal and 0.3592 V at the negative terminal. Continuity across the relay contacts is nominal with a measured resistance of 0.01 Ω, matching the expected value. No irregularities in voltage or continuity were observed during this test.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Module-to-module cable connections (between modules),
description: Test all fast-connection terminals and cables connecting each module (power supply to ambient sensor, ambient sensor to load module) for intermittent contact or unstable connection that could lead to periodic voltage interruptions at the load., outcome='All inspected cable connections show that (+) cables are connected to (+) terminals and (−) cables are connected to (−) terminals, with no polarity inversions detected. The physical connections appear stable with no indicated issues from the inspections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=90.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0), ('inspect_connections', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
